  "text": "In Fig. 5 in Appendix A.8, we show how the sample entropy H(p) decays and the index histograms develop during training, as the network learns to condense most of the weights to a couple of centers when optimizing [CITATION_1] . In contrast, the methods of [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] manually impose 0 as the most frequent center by pruning ≈ 80% of the network weights. We note that the recent works by [CITATION_5] also manages to tackle the problem in a single training procedure, using the minimum description length principle. In contrast to our framework, they take a Bayesian perspective and rely on a parametric assumption on the symbol distribution.",
